post_text:
The Strasburg C-3 School District is now hiring substitute teachers. To be a substitute teacher, you must have a Substitute Teaching Certificate from the Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) and successfully complete a FBI/Highway Patrol background check.

A Substitute Teaching Certificate has required a minimum of 60 college hours. Yesterday, the State Board of Education passed an emergency amendment to allow substitute teachers to be certified with 20 hours of online training as an alternative to the current requirement of 60 hours of college credit. The emergency rule will take effect on September 2, 2020. Additional information regarding the online training, including approved vendors and associated costs, can be found here, once available- https://dese.mo.gov/educator-quality/certification/substitute-teachers.

Substitute teacher pay is $75.00/day.

For more information on becoming a substitute, contact Chrystal Mayfield or Julie Fields at 816-680-3333

STRASBURG SCHOOL DISTRICT
OPEN ENROLLMENT INFORMATION

TWO OPTIONS FOR ENROLLMENT:

1. Beginning August 3rd stop by the school Monday through Thursday 8:00-2:00 pick up an enrollment pack. Take it home, fill it out and return it to the school office prior to August 12, 2020.

2. Beginning August 3rd call the school office at 816-680-3333 and schedule an appointment to enroll for one of the following days:

August 10th 8:00-3:00
August 11th 8:00-5:00
August 12th 8:00-3:00

NEEDED DOCUMENTATION:
Kindergarten students and new students to the district need to bring immunization records, birth certificates, proof of residency, and social security cards.

Current students need to bring proof of residency and updated immunization records (8th grade students will have updated shot requirements).

First, this event is a replacement for the Mom/Son Basketball. We will not be having a basketball game at a later date. I think there was some confusion about that. We are changing it up a bit to see if we can get a higher percentage of boys to participate!

Hi friends! We need your help. A dinner is being provided for the Yates family on Wednesday evening. I have been in touch with the Strasburg PTO as they are the ones overseeing the dinner. They have asked if we can provide the drinks for the event. They are preparing for 250 people. They have also asked if we can provide 5 volunteers to keep food trays full, etc. it is probably easiest to purchase cans of soda, bottled water and tea. If you would like to help provide drinks or help that evening. If you are donating drinks please drop them off at Lone Jack Elementary by Wednesday morning if possible. If you are volunteering, please arrive at the civic center by 4:45. Please let me know. The dinner is slated to start at 5:00pm.

post_text:
Yesterday afternoon, two young siblings and members of our Strasburg family were killed in a car accident. With an extremely heavy heart, we are asking for help from the community, family, and friends to ease the burden of funeral costs for this family. One hundred percent of any proceeds raised will go to cover funeral costs and any surplus will be used to help the family in any way needed. Donations can be given to Mr. Arnone at the school, put in the mail dropbox at M.R. Riley, CPA (located at 316 W 58 Hwy, Strasburg), or handed directly to Katie Wingard. Checks can be made out to Strasburg PTO. There is also a GoFundMe set up for those who prefer to give their support that way and for those who are not local.

https://www.gofundme.com/f/funeral-costs-for-yates-family?utm_source=customer&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=p_cf+share-flow-1

Please share.

post_text: Invitations to the all new Mother(ly)/Son Superhero dance will be coming home soon with all Strasburg boys. We are excited for this new event! There will be pizza, prizes, competitions, photos, and plenty of dancing! The request to RSVP was inadvertently left off the invite, but it would really help us out to have an idea of how many people will be attending. We will also need several adult volunteers to help run various aspects of the event. Maybe Dad could help out while Mom is hanging out with her super son. To RSVP or to volunteer to help out, please email us at strasburgpto1@gmail.com, comment on this post, or message us. Thank you!!

post_text:
Free family holiday fun this weekend!

Please feel free to share. In an effort to provide families with an opportunity for some free holiday fun, the First Christian Church is hosting a Family Fun Festival this Saturday starting at 10:30. Pictures include the store where children can shop for their parents' gifts and then have the opportunity to wrap those gifts. For a craft, they can make the snowman ornament. Our computer lab will be open providing some holiday fun. Other activities include cookie decorating, a service project for St. Jude Children's Hospital, face painting, games, and even a free lunch. The church is located at 519 Cedar St. Remember...everything is free.

post_text:
After what we felt was a wonderful suggestion from a parent, we have decided to change up how we are doing this at the auction. Instead of kids bidding, each item will be a part of a raffle. This allows each kid to have a chance of winning, regardless of the amount of money spent. Kids (or parents on behalf of kids) can buy raffle tickets and choose which experience they would like to put them toward. They can put all of them in the same one or in all different ones! You DO NOT have to be present to win. Ticket prices will be:

2 for $1
12 for $5
25 for $10
60 for $20

Please share and spread the word!

post_text: Do you like it when the odds are in your favor? If so, have I got a deal for you.... Turn in a craft for the homemade craft contest at our auction! Winner gets a $25 gift card to Hobby Lobby. At this moment, you would have a 100% chance of winning because we have zero items! Nada. Zilch. Big fat goose egg. Maybe YOU can help us change that! Items can be almost anything - as long as you put your blood, sweat, and tears into it. Well, maybe not all that, but as long as you made it or refurbished it! Items can be turned into the office no later than Friday. They must be clearly marked with your name and 'Craft Contest'.

Box Tops for Education
August 15, 2019 at 10:35 AM ·

Your top questions, answered!
Yes! Keep clipping regular Box Tops and sending them to your schools as long as you continue to find them on packages. Your school will still get credit for all Box Tops validly submitted by your school’s coordinator. (Don’t send in the new Box Tops icon used to mark products that are eligible for Box Tops earnings via receipt scan in the new Box Tops App.)
Remember to scan your receipt in the Box Tops App, too: most brand teams are awarding both the receipt scan earnings and the traditional Clip earnings for a single item purchase during this time of transition.

post_text: Please help us by signing up to provide some food for the Father(ly)/Daughter Dance on Feb. 2nd. Non-refrigerated food can be dropped off Friday, Feb 1st at school, no later than 3:30pm. Food can also be dropped off at the Memorial building in Pleasant Hill on Saturday, the 2nd from 10am - 1pm and from 5-6pm. This list is just suggestions, and we welcome other ideas. We could have approximately 100 people at the dance. Cupcakes and punch will be provided. If you would like to help, but are unable to drop food off at those times, please contact the PTO at strasburgpto1@gmail.com or message us on Facebook. Thank you!

post_text: Thank you so much to everyone who came out to support us at the chili supper and auction! Thank you Dave Dodson Auctions for doing our live auction for us! It was a great success! Congratulations to Jennifer Miller who won our 50/50 drawing! Also, congratulations to Kim Ross who won the drawing for signing up for basket donations.

post_text:
My Oh My! We have some fantastic items to bid on! Come on out Saturday for some delicious chili and some auction fun. Food is served from 4-6pm. First silent auction table closes at 5:30pm, last one 7:30pm. We are having a LIVE auction by Dave Dodson auctions at 6:30! Items in the live auction are:
-We Love Mom Basket
-We Love Dad Basket
-Outdoor Adventure Basket
-Chiefs Basket
-American Girl Doll (Tenney)
-Fire Ring
-Front row seats to Strasburg music concerts and graduation
-50% Off Orthodontic Treatment
-Certificate for 4 Cases of Beer from Boulevard
-Starter Acoustic Guitar
-Handcrafted Porch Swing made by our very own Mr. Arnone!

Hope to see you there!!

post_text: The auction is less than one week away! If you are entering an item in the craft contest, please turn it into the school office this week and clearly mark it with your name and that it is for the craft contest. (If it is not marked, it may accidentally end up as a regular auction item) It helps if we have items before Friday, but they will still be accepted until Friday after school. Thank you for your participation!
